title: History of Music in Western Culture II
description: Second part of intensive historical, analytical, and cultural-aesthetic examination of music in Western culture from the ninth through the twenty-first centuries. Considers both instrumental and vocal repertories, from the Baroque to the Romantic, c. 1600–1830. Prerequisites: MUS 120A. Music majors should be enrolled concurrently in MUS 101B. Department stamp required for nonmajors.
